<P>
MAKING ROOM FOR 'LIFE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Finally, there is an intelligent show for teen-agers, I don't have much time 
to watch TV, but I make time for "My So-Called Life" (ABC) on Thursdays.This 
show addresses adolescent issues with sensitivity and realism, unlike other 
well-established shows ("Full House," etc.). I hope the ABC producers keep the 
show on long enough to attract the attention it deserves. 
</P>
<P>
 Melissa Cheney, Rancho Santa Fe 
</P>
