<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 NORTH OF RELIANCE: A Personal Story of Living Beyond the Wilderness by Dave 
Olesen (Northword Press, Box 1360, Minocqua, Wis. 54548: $12.95; 160 pp., 
illustrated, paperback original). Olesen rejects the madness Bogosian 
celebrates for life in the wilderness near the Great Slave Lake. Unlike many 
neo-pioneers, he never romanticizes his decision or portrays himself as 
conquering nature. Instead of pitting himself against the harsh climate of 
northern Canada, Olesen strives to adapt his life to its rhythms. He writes 
about his successes and failures in spare, honest prose, in an expanded journal 
that reveals the beauty of the bleak northern forests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
