<TEXT>
<P>
 WATCH IT MADE IN THE U.S.A.: A Visitor's Guide to the Companies That Make Your 
Favorite Products by Bruce Brumberg and Karen Axelrod (John Muir Publications: 
$16.95; 295 pp., illustrated, paperback original). Brumberg and Axelrod have 
compiled a list of companies that offer tours of their factories, either for 
free or at a nominal charge.Visitors can see ice cream being made (Ben & 
Jerry's, Vermont); glass being blown (Corning Glass Center, New York); bourbon 
distilled (Wild Turkey, Kentucky); chips being fried (Frito-Lay, Washington) 
and Hostess Twinkies being filled (Continental Bakery, Massachusetts). In 
places, the upbeat text reads a little too much like a press release, but 
people looking for unusual stops on their next vacation should consult "Watch 
It Made." 
</P>
