<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITIC'S PICK: 'THE TIMES OF HARVEY MILK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robert Epstein and Richard Schmeichen's 1984 Academy Award-winning documentary 
is a powerful, comprehensive yet incisive study of the political career and 
assassination of the San Francisco supervisor, one of the nation's first openly 
gay elected officials (Bravo Thursday at 9:30 p.m., Friday at 2 p.m.). Kevin 
Thomas 
</P>
