<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding David Mennie's letter about Eddie Vedder (Dec. 4): 
</P>
<P>
 For one, Pearl Jam is far from being overrated, and you would know that if you 
stopped listening to the media and actually listened to the group's music. 
</P>
<P>
 You would realize that the lyrics come from deep down in Eddie's soul.Give 
them a chance, and if you don't like their music, don't listen! 
</P>
<P>
 It's simple. Pearl Jam is only five decent men trying to make an honest 
living, and they seem to be doing all right. 
</P>
<P>
 P.S. Queensryche went out with the Hula-Hoop. Pearl Jam rules Seattle now, and 
still will rule Seattle a long time from now. 
</P>
<P>
