</P>
<P>
 North Hills 
</P>
<P>
 I know the media talks way too much about Eddie Vedder and Pearl Jam, 
especially because they don't like all the publicity. But if there is anyone to 
be given credit to, it's them. 
</P>
<P>
 I just had to say something after I read some responses to Nov. 20 article 
"All Revved Up," putting them down and thinking they are doing everything for 
money and fame. 
</P>
<P>
 If they wanted money, they would not have canceled their tour last summer to 
fight with Ticketmaster so their fans could pay less for concert tickets. They 
could have easily gone on tour, made a lot of money and not have looked like 
bad guys, because they would just be going along with the system like other 
bands. 
</P>
<P>
 If there is anyone to look up to in this corrupt and greedy society, it's 
Pearl Jam. 
</P>
<P>
