<HEADLINE>
<P>
A PATIENT THANKFUL FOR SURGICAL TEAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 My compliments to Kathleen Doheny and Paul Morse for "Team Players" (Nov. 29). 
</P>
<P>
 Having received a triple bypass in August, I thank God for the team players my 
doctor David Minna helped assemble at Long Beach Memorial Medical Center. I 
always had the feeling that I, the patient, came first. 
</P>
<P>
 I assure you I offered prayers of thanksgiving that they paid attention in 
medical school to be able to perform the miracle of saving my life. I say to 
the surgical teams existing now and to those studying medicine, thank you for 
your dedication and God bless you. 
</P>
<P>
 NORMAN BRADY 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 
</P>
