<P>
SICILIAN STORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I enjoyed "Blood and Watermelon" (Nov. 13) by Rita Giordano. Ms. Giordano 
shares the same surname as my "nonna" (grandmother), although my nonna was 
Sicilian. I couldn't help but wonder if Ms. Giordano's nonna would turn over in 
her grave if, after all, her bloodline was Sicilian -- "the wild land of wild 
people" -- and not from the north "land of Italian kings." 
</P>
<P>
 KATHERINE GRECO 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego 
