</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dennis Hunt 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Barry Manilow, "Singin' With the Big Bands," (***) Arista. Flashing exemplary 
big-band crooner form, Manilow glides through swing favorites, wisely using the 
original arrangements (with a stronger rhythm-section emphasis).He's smoothly 
supported by current editions of famous bands on what is easily his finest 
album. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Hunt 
</P>
</TEXT>
