<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MALIBU; DEADLINE NEARS FOR CITY NONPROFIT GROUPS TO APPLY FOR 
FEDERAL FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Local nonprofit organizations providing social services in the city must 
submit applications by Dec. 30 to be eligible for Community Development Block 
Grant funds. 
</P>
<P>
 The federal government has allocated $75,000 annually to the city for the 
programs.Eligible organizations must provide services directly to local 
residents who are defined by the federal government as having low to moderate 
incomes. 
</P>
<P>
 Access to the community grant money is open to nonprofit agencies and 
organizations that are recognized by the federal and state government. The city 
also welcomes proposals for new services. 
</P>
<P>
 Programs funded with the grant money include Malibu Labor Exchange, Meals on 
Wheels and child-care services at the Malibu Community Center at Point Dume. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will begin distributing the funds in July. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council will consider applicants and their respective awards at the 
Jan. 23 meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications can be picked up at City Hall, 23555 Civic Center Way. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 456-2489. KATHLEEN KELLEHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
