<P>
STEPHEN A. GAYMONT; BACTERIOLOGIST INTRODUCED YOGURT TO U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stephen A. Gaymont, 89, a bacteriologist credited with introducing yogurt to 
the United States in the early 1940s.Gaymont also invented frozen yogurt, which 
he marketed under the name "Yogo." He was the founder and retired president of 
Gaymont Laboratories Inc., which produced the culture that enabled more than 
500 companies to make a product that has the taste of sour cream, but only 
one-sixth the calories. Gaymont, who came to the United States in 1939, started 
his laboratory company in New York and moved it to Chicago in 1944. In Chicago 
on Friday. 
