<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL PLAYOFFS; YOUNGSTOWN STATE'S DOMINANCE CONTINUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By REPLACEMENT  
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Defending champion Youngstown State, playing in its fourth consecutive NCAA 
I-AA championship game, got two scoring runs and a touchdown pass from 
quarterback Mark Brungard to defeat Boise State, 28-14, Saturday in Huntington, 
W.Va. 
</P>
<P>
 Youngstown State (14-0-1) has won three of the last four championship games, 
losing only to Marshall in 1992. Boise State finished 13-2. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Westminster (Pa.) 27, Pacific Lutheran 7 -- Andy Blatt rushed for 128 yards, 
scored once and connected with Tim McNeil on a 60-yard touchdown pass play 
after taking a pitchout as the Titans (12-2) won their sixth NAIA Division II 
title with a victory over the defending champion Lutes (11-2). 
