<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCCER; GARFIELD CRUISES TO VICTORY ON CORDOBA'S HAT TRICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Garfield (4-0-1) rode Romeo Cordoba's hat trick to a 5-0 victory over South 
Gate (0-6) in a Southeastern Conference match Thursday. Cordoba tallied his 
first goal in the 15th minute off a pass from Fermin Diaz.In the 22nd minute, 
Cordoba caught the Ram goalkeeper off guard and smashed the ball home on a 
corner kick. Cordoba then scored on a free kick in the 50th minute, putting the 
game well out of reach.  
</P>
<P>
 Ivan Valiente and Gerardo Gomez rounded out the scoring for the Bulldogs in 
the 60th and 78th minutes of the match. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 2, University 2 -- The visiting Romans (4-1-1) overcame a two-goal 
halftime deficit to tie the match, 2-2, in a Coastal Conference game Thursday. 
Roman forward Brook Berhanu notched his seventh goal of the season in the 45th 
minute and Bairon Calles scored the equalizer in the 60th. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell 1, Jordan 0 -- The unbeaten Eagles had a rough time with the Bulldogs but 
won a Southeastern Conference matchup at Jordan on Thursday. Bell forward 
Sergio Ramirez scored on an assist from Jose Leal to keep the Eagles' 
undefeated at 4-0-3. The Bulldogs fell to 2-3-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt 2, Huntington Park 0 -- The Roughriders won a tough battle over the 
Spartans at Huntington Park in a Southeastern Conference matchup. 
</P>
<P>
 Vicente Mejia scored on cross from Fernando Jimenez and Jesus Perez also 
tallied for the Roughriders (2-1-3). 
</P>
<P>
 The match referees called the game early because of misbehavior from the 
crowd. Spartans coach Herman Weller said he would protest he referee's 
decision. 
</P>
<P>
 Belmont 1, Franklin 0 -- Hector Alvarado scored on a perfect pass from Pedro 
Orellana to keep Belmont a perfect 7-0 on the season in a victory at Franklin. 
</P>
