<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; April Jackson, ; Len Hall 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BEARING DOWN: Rams countdown to St. Louis: Two games left? The Rams -- hurting 
statistically on both offense and defense -- are trying to break a five-game 
losing streak against the Bears in Chicago today (C11) . . . Actually, some in 
Los Angeles may want the Bears to play well. A Chicago baking company donates 
one case of brownies for each Bear touchdown to a different children's hospital 
each week. This week's recipient is L.A.'s Childrens Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 SKIPPING TOWN? Somebody forgot to tell the whales that Orange County isn't a 
popular place right now. Whale-watching season is on, and ocean buffs have seen 
more than one whale each of the last few days lumbering down the coast in 
search of Baja's warmer waters. . . . Dana Point Sportfishing has started daily 
whale boat runs at 10, noon, and 2 ($12 adults, $7 for small children). Newport 
Landing Sportfishing starts whale runs Dec. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 REINVENTING NATURE: You can't build a house in a hollowed-out rock -- like 
architect Brion S. Jeannette is doing at Aliso Beach (E1) -- without facing a 
few problems. Such as: replanting the original coastal sage scrub on top of the 
rock at the project's finish. . . . Says Jeannette, who must duplicate the 
rock's original drainage pattern: "If our drainage retains too much rain water, 
the plants will grow too much and the rock will look like a Chia pet." 
</P>
<P>
 SANTA IN SYDNEY: When do you send your kids away for Christmas? When they have 
a chance to spend the holidays playing baseball in Australia. Seattle Mariners 
scout Myron Pines, who lives and teaches in Garden Grove, is taking a group of 
30 teen-age boys to Australia this week for an 18-and-under tournament. . . . 
Each is paying his own way. Pines, who hopes he has enough adult escorts, 
suggests: "With it being Christmas, we think the boys will probably be on 
pretty good behavior. They're all certainly excited." 
</P>
<P>
 (BEGIN TEXT OF INFOBOX / INFOGRAPHIC) Pre-St. Louis Blues 
</P>
<P>
 Some seasonal average stats tell the story of the Rams' 4-10 record so far. 
Out of 28 teams, they rank: 
</P>
<P>
 PER-GAME OFFENSE Rushing: 24th Passing: 15th Points: 21st **** 
</P>
<P>
