<P>
LEONARD AGEE SHELTON; FORMER CITY ATTORNEY FOR POMONA, COVINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Leonard Agee Shelton, 83, former city attorney for Pomona, Covina and other 
San Gabriel Valley cities. A native of Ardmore, Okla., Shelton moved to 
California as a child and was educated at Pomona College and Boalt Hall School 
of Law.He began his career in Santa Monica. He served as a supply officer at 
Wright-Patterson Air Force Base near Dayton, Ohio, during World War II, earning 
the Legion of Merit. After the war, Shelton founded the Pomona-based law firm 
of Allard, Shelton and O'Connor, where he practiced until his retirement last 
year. Among his clients, in addition to Pomona and Covina, were the cities of 
Claremont, La Verne and Glendora. He served on the Pomona College Board of 
Trustees from 1956 until 1981 and was the board's general counsel and secretary 
from 1981 until 1991. A bird watcher and conservationist, Shelton served on the 
national boards of the Audubon Society and the International Crane Foundation 
and worked to preserve wetlands and other natural habitats. On Dec. 7 in 
Claremont. 
