became worse. The teachers and many social workers have not been guaranteed 
their paychecks after December. I then learned about San Jose High School, 
which declared bankruptcy a couple years ago. The school closed for a month and 
almost all of the teachers were furloughed and all the elective classes cut. 
</P>
