PREP ROUNDUP; NO. 6 IRVINE WINS COAST WRESTLING CLASSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Justin Meier and Steve Ruiz finished first as sixth-ranked Irvine won the 
Coast Wrestling Classic at Santa Cruz High School. The tournament, which had 37 
participants, is considered a warm-up for the Fountain Valley Five Counties 
tournament, which is held in January. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine finished with 168 points, only five ahead of second-place Shingle 
Springs Pondersoa and third-place Madera (154 1/2). 
</P>
<P>
 Meier, who wrestled at 130 pounds, pinned second-seeded Ruben Guttierez of San 
Jose Overfelt in one minute 21 seconds to win the championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruiz won at 189 pounds by defeating Orinda Miramonte's Justin Soucy, 4-0, in 
the finals. 
</P>
<P>
 Andrew Pena finished second at 119 pounds, losing to George Moreno in the 
finals, 20-11. To reach the finals, however, Pena pinned top-seeded Max Taylor 
in the semifinals in 3:10. 
</P>
<P>
 Cris Testerman went 6-1, with three pins to finish third, defeating Oakdale's 
David Sturtevant by injury default. 
</P>
<P>
 Peter Hamilton, who as 4-2 at 112 pounds, finished fifth by defeating Cesar 
Arias of Firebaugh, 12-2. 
</P>
<P>
 At 125 pounds, Jeremy Brown also finished fifth, pinning Santa Cruz Harbor's 
Tyler Dominguez in four minutes 16 seconds. 
</P>
