<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL / BOLSA GRANDE CHRISTMAS CLASSIC; LATE FREE THROWS SEAL 
VICTORY FOR TRABUCO HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sarah Warnick broke a 59-59 tie with two free throws in the late going to help 
lead Trabuco Hills to a 67-64 victory over Montebello Cantwell Sacred Heart on 
Saturday night in the championship game of the Bolsa Grande Christmas Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 Warnick followed with two more free throws and a field goal before fouling out 
with 1 minute 12 seconds left, when the Mustangs had a three-point edge.It was 
Trabuco Hills' first girls' basketball tournament title. 
</P>
<P>
 LaShieka Henderson, tournament most valuable player, had 22 points and 13 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills (8-2) overcame a 16-9 first-quarter deficit to take a 33-26 lead 
at halftime. Leading the way was Henderson, who scored 13 points in the second 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Cantwell Sacred Heart (8-2) outscored the Mustangs, 11-2, to open the fourth 
quarter and built a 57-51 lead before Trabuco Hills recovered and outscored the 
Cardinals, 16-7, for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Dyanna Hatch contributed three three-pointers and 18 points for Trabuco Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have the potential to be a good team, but we still haven't jelled," said 
Trabuco Hills Coach Howard Stephens, noting the team had to overcome 37 
turnovers in the contest. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 In the third-place game: 
</P>
<P>
 Westminster 43, Capistrano Valley 39 -- Amber Farroux converted on a 
three-point play with 27 seconds left, breaking a 39-39 tie, to lead the Lions. 
She had 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In a consolation game: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 61, Magnolia 47 -- Heather Hollis scored 24 points and had 20 
rebounds as San Clemente (5-5) won the fifth-place game. 
</P>
<P>
 Stacy Tewell had 15 points for Magnolia (3-5). MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
