<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CHAPMAN DOESN'T BLOW IT, DEFEATS REDLANDS, 77-57 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A week after blowing a halftime lead and losing to Redlands, Chapman put away 
the Bulldogs in the second half, and won, 77-57, in a nonconference men's 
basketball game Saturday at Chapman University. 
</P>
<P>
 The Panthers (5-3) led by six at the break, but outscored Redlands, 30-21, in 
the first 12 minutes of the second half to put the game out of reach. 
</P>
<P>
 In a game at Redlands on Dec. 10, Chapman had a five-point halftime lead but 
was outscored, 34-7, in the first 10 minutes of the second half and lost, 
87-80. 
</P>
<P>
 But behind Stefan Mumaw, the Panthers were able to turn things around, as the 
6-foot-8 center had 20 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Mumaw had 15 of his points in the first half as Chapman led by as many as 11 
before Redlands' Steve Reed hit a three-pointer at the buzzer to make it 37-31. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bulldogs cut Chapman's lead to 39-37 four minutes into the second half, 
but three-pointers from Anthony Gonzales and Jeff Reeves put the Panthers ahead 
by seven with 12:20 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Redlands never got closer than six the rest of the way and Chapman built a 
65-50 lead on consecutive baskets from Corey Klinke, who finished with 11 
points. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Dzierzynski, who scored 31 against Redlands last week, was held to eight 
points but he had 12 assists. DAN ARRITT 
</P>
