<P>
WOMAN ARRESTED ON 3 WARRANTS WALKS OUT BACK DOOR OF COSTA MESA JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From A Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 53-year-old woman escaped from the city jail early Saturday, about two hours 
after she was arrested on burglary warrants, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Betty Jane Willis of Santa Ana slipped out a door in the back of the jail, 
Costa Mesa Police Lt. Alan Kent said. 
</P>
<P>
 "She walked through a door that was left ajar," Kent said. "We are unable to 
locate her at this point." 
</P>
<P>
 Willis was arrested about midnight at Bay Street and Newport Boulevard on 
charges of driving with a suspended license and providing false information, 
Kent said. Police also discovered that the woman had three warrants -- two for 
burglary and one for narcotics paraphernalia, he said. 
</P>
