<HEADLINE>
<P>
COURT REAFFIRMS DIM VIEW OF 3 MILLION YULE LIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state Supreme Court has refused to set aside its order dimming a man's 
eye-popping display of 3 million Christmas lights. 
</P>
<P>
 After neighbors filed a lawsuit, Jennings Osborne was ordered Dec. 5 to tone 
down his display enough to reduce the crowds that have been drawn to his 
well-to-do neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
 Osborne asked the court to let him turn on the lights and music at his home 
while the U.S. Supreme Court reviews whether his religious rights were 
violated. He also argued that the high court's ruling was too broad. Both 
arguments were rejected in Friday's decision. 
</P>
