<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN WALKS OUT OF COSTA MESA JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 53-year-old woman escaped from the city jail early Saturday, about two hours 
after she was arrested on a traffic violation and subsequently was found to 
have outstanding burglary and drug warrants, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Betty Jane Willis of Santa Ana slipped out a door in the back of the jail, 
said Costa Mesa Police Lt. Alan Kent. 
</P>
<P>
 "She walked through a door that was left ajar," Kent said. 
</P>
<P>
 Willis was arrested shortly after midnight at Bay Street and Newport Boulevard 
for driving with a suspended license and providing false information, Kent 
said. Police then discovered the woman had three outstanding warrants -- two 
for burglary and one for possession of narcotics paraphernalia, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are seeking help in capturing Willis and asked that anyone with 
information call Costa Mesa police at (714) 754-5280. 
</P>
</TEXT>
